Ora che il tema grafico è sistemato, concentriamoci sulla parte tecnica dati + rating.

Obiettivo di questo step:
1) Definire bene i tipi TypeScript in `types.ts`
2) Implementare un motore di rating per la pallavolo in `lib/ratingSystem.ts`
3) Creare dati mock realistici in `services/mockService.ts`
4) Integrare rating e statistiche in Dashboard, PlayerProfile, Leaderboard e Scouting (solo lettura per ora)

────────────────────────────────────────
1) TYPES – definisci/modifica `types.ts`

Assicurati che ci siano almeno questi tipi:

```ts
export type PlayerPosition =
  | 'setter'
  | 'opposite'
  | 'outside_hitter'
  | 'middle_blocker'
  | 'libero';

export interface Player {
  id: string;
  teamId: string;
  firstName: string;
  lastName: string;
  shirtNumber: number;
  position: PlayerPosition;
  region?: string;
  province?: string;
  averageRating?: number; // calcolato lato servizio/mock
}

export interface Match {
  id: string;
  teamId: string;
  opponentName: string;
  competitionName: string;
  matchDate: string; // ISO string
  homeAway: 'home' | 'away';
}

export type Phase = 'K1' | 'K2' | 'transition';

export type Fundamental =
  | 'attack'
  | 'serve'
  | 'reception'
  | 'block'
  | 'defense'
  | 'error_other';

export interface Event {
  id: string;
  matchId: string;
  playerId: string;
  setNumber: number;
  rallyNumber: number;
  phase: Phase;
  fundamental: Fundamental;
  outcomeCode: string;
  isImportantPoint: boolean;
  isDecisivePoint: boolean;
}

export interface PlayerMatchStats {
  matchId: string;
  playerId: string;
  teamId: string;
  rating: number;
  breakdown: {
    attack: number;
    serve: number;
    reception: number;
    block: number;
    defense: number;
  };
  totals: {
    attacks: number;
    attackPoints: number;
    attackErrors: number;
    serves: number;
    aces: number;
    serveErrors: number;
    receptions: number;
    perfectReceptions: number;
    negativeReceptions: number;
    blocks: number;
    blockPoints: number;
    digs: number;
  };
}
Mantieni anche i tipi User, UserRole ecc. già presenti, adattandoli se serve.

────────────────────────────────────────
2) MOTORE DI RATING – lib/ratingSystem.ts

Implementa una funzione principale:

